<meta name="SEO.Description" content="The system, dubbed &amp;lsquo;Boat Trap&amp;rsquo;, uses ballistic nets dropped from aircraft to ensnare and stop small boats without using lethal force. The Boat Trap has been extensively tested in both US waters and in the Caribbean. It is currently being deployed on a limited basis by US government agencies. &amp;lsquo;The Boat Trap has been designed specifically to stop small boats in crowded areas, said Anderson Leveille, founder of Moscow Mills Manufacturing. &amp;lsquo;These small, often high speed craft, whether operated by pirates, terrorists or drug smugglers, are a constant threat. Because these small boats tend to operate close to shore and" />
